         <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.2604" xml:lang="en">
            <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
            <dateline>Dominica. W. I. <lb/> 10 April 1885.</dateline>
            <opener>My dear Sir,</opener>
            <p>I regret exceedingly the delay in keeping my promise to send you the patois proverbs/sayings. I have been endeavouring, however, to obtain as complete a series as possible, and to that end I entered into correspondence with a gentleman, here, who has a complete knowledge of our people and their language.<note n="1" place="foot" type="editorial"> Gemeint ist vermutlich <persName ref="[authorityLink]">Frederick Sterns-Fadelle</persName>. Er wird als “a Creole of French descent, educated at the University of Paris“ (<bibl>


Paravisini-Gebert
</bibl> 2008:260) beschrieben.</note> I will send you the paper by next mail without fail, and <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/> I trust they will not be too late for your purpose.</p>
            <closer>
               <salute>I am,<lb/>Yours faithfully</salute>
               <signed>
                  <persName ref="[authorityLink]">H. A. Alford Nicholls</persName>
               </signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>Prof. H. Schuchardt</p>
            </postscript>
